{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb78cd47b-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s401"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"401"},"text":"§ 401.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this chapter:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb78cd47c-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s401/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Establishment","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term “establishment” means the Department of Agriculture, Commerce, Defense, Education, Energy, Health and Human Services, Housing and Urban Development, the Interior, Justice, Labor, State, Transportation, Homeland Security, the Treasury, or Veterans Affairs; the Agency for International Development, the Community Development Financial Institutions Fund, the Environmental Protection Agency, the Federal Communications Commission, the Federal Emergency Management Agency, the General Services Administration, the National Aeronautics and Space Administration, the Nuclear Regulatory Commission, the Office of Personnel Management, the Railroad Retirement Board, the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, the Small Business Administration, the Corporation for National and Community Service, the Social Security Administration, the Federal Housing Finance Agency, the Tennessee Valley Authority, the Export-Import Bank of the United States, the Commissions established under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s15301"},"text":"section 15301 of title 40","children":[],"tail":", the National Security Agency, or the National Reconnaissance Office, as the case may be."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb78cd47d-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s401/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Federal agency","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term “Federal agency” means an agency as defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s552/f"},"text":"section 552(f) of this title","children":[],"tail":" (including an establishment as defined in paragraph (1)), but shall not be construed to include the Government Accountability Office."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb78cd47e-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s401/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Head of the establishment","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term “head of the establishment” means the Secretary of Agriculture, Commerce, Defense, Education, Energy, Health and Human Services, Housing and Urban Development, the Interior, Labor, State, Transportation, Homeland Security, the Treasury, or Veterans Affairs; the Attorney General; the Administrator of the Agency for International Development, Environmental Protection, General Services, National Aeronautics and Space, Small Business, or the Federal Emergency Management Agency; the Director of the Office of Personnel Management; the Chairman of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission, the Federal Communications Commission, or the Railroad Retirement Board; the Chief Executive Officer of the Corporation for National and Community Service; the Administrator of the Community Development Financial Institutions Fund; the Chairperson of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation; the Commissioner of Social Security, Social Security Administration; the Director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency; the Board of Directors of the Tennessee Valley Authority; the President of the Export-Import Bank of the United States; the Federal Cochairpersons of the Commissions established under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s15301"},"text":"section 15301 of title 40","children":[],"tail":"; the Director of the National Security Agency; or the Director of the National Reconnaissance Office; as the case may be."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb78cd47f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s401/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Inspector general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term “Inspector General” means the Inspector General of an establishment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb78cd480-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s401/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Office","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term “Office” means the Office of Inspector General of an establishment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb78cd481-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286/s3/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–286, § 3(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/4207"},"text":"136 Stat. 4207","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb78cd482-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"prospectiveAmendment","id":"idb78cd483-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments Not Shown in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section was derived from section 12 of the Inspector General Act of 1978, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/452"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–452","children":[],"tail":", which was set out in the former Appendix to this title, and as it existed as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-10-19"},"text":"Oct. 19, 2021","children":[],"tail":". "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/452/s12"},"text":"Section 12 of Pub. L. 95–452","children":[],"tail":" was amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/dE/tLII"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, div. E, title LII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 5202(b), 5272(10), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/3227"},"text":"136 Stat. 3227","children":[],"tail":", 3241, prior to being repealed and reenacted as this section by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–286","children":[],"tail":", §§ 3(b), 7, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/4207"},"text":"136 Stat. 4207","children":[],"tail":", 4361. For applicability of those amendments to this section, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286/s5/b"},"text":"section 5(b) of Pub. L. 117–286","children":[],"tail":", set out in a Transitional and Savings Provisions note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":". "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/452/s12"},"text":"Section 12 of Pub. L. 95–452","children":[],"tail":" was amended as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(1) in paragraph (3) [enacted by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–286","children":[],"tail":" as paragraph (4) of this section] by inserting “except as otherwise expressly provided,” before “the term”; and"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(2) by striking “and” at the end of paragraph (4), by substituting “; and” for the period at the end of paragraph (5), and by adding at the end the following:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"“(6) the term ‘appropriate congressional committees’ means—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"“(A) the Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs of the Senate;","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) the Committee on Oversight and Reform of the House of Representatives; and","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"“(C) any other relevant congressional committee or subcommittee of jurisdiction.”","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/452/s12"},"text":"Section 12 of Pub. L. 95–452","children":[],"tail":" began with “the term” in paragraphs (1) to (5) and ended with semicolons in paragraphs (1) to (3), “; and” in paragraph (4), and a period in paragraph (5). As restated by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–286","children":[],"tail":", the text of paragraphs (1) to (5) began with “The term” and all ended with periods."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb78cd484-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idb78cd485-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"401","children":[],"tail"